<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q64_v9" title="Q64_v9" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>En una bolsa hay 36 caramelos: algunos son ácidos y los demás no ácidos. Al sacar un caramelo al azar, la probabilidad de que sea no ácido es 
      <m:math>
        <m:mfrac>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
          <m:mn>4</m:mn>
        </m:mfrac>
      </m:math>.
    </p>
    <p>Se proponen las siguientes descripciones sobre la cantidad de caramelos ácidos y no ácidos en la bolsa. ¿Cuál de ellas es coherente con la probabilidad dada?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">Hay 12 caramelos ácidos y 24 no ácidos.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si hay 24 caramelos no ácidos de un total de 36, entonces la probabilidad de sacar un caramelo no ácido es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>24</m:mn><m:mn>36</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> no es igual a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">Hay 9 caramelos ácidos y 27 no ácidos.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Si hay 27 caramelos no ácidos de un total de 36, entonces la probabilidad de sacar un caramelo no ácido es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>27</m:mn><m:mn>36</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>. Además, <m:math><m:mn>36</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>27</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn></m:math>, así que la descripción es coherente.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">Hay 18 caramelos ácidos y 18 no ácidos.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si hay 18 caramelos no ácidos de un total de 36, entonces la probabilidad de sacar un caramelo no ácido es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mn>36</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> no es igual a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">Hay 24 caramelos ácidos y 12 no ácidos.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si hay 12 caramelos no ácidos de un total de 36, entonces la probabilidad de sacar un caramelo no ácido es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mn>36</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> no es igual a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar qué representa la probabilidad dada</strong></p>
            <p>La probabilidad de sacar un caramelo no ácido es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math>. Eso significa que <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> del total de caramelos son no ácidos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular cuántos caramelos no ácidos hay</strong></p>
            <p>Como en total hay 36 caramelos, la cantidad de no ácidos es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>36</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>36</m:mn><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>108</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>27</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Entonces hay 27 caramelos no ácidos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular cuántos caramelos ácidos hay</strong></p>
            <p>Como el total es 36, la cantidad de ácidos es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>36</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>27</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Entonces hay 9 caramelos ácidos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La descripción que coincide con 9 caramelos ácidos y 27 no ácidos es la alternativa B.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La opción correcta es <strong>ChoiceB</strong>: hay 9 caramelos ácidos y 27 no ácidos.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>